    <subsection>
        <title>Division</title>
        
        <p>Whenever we share fairly, we are using <term>division</term>. Many delicious chocolate bars are made using molds so they can be quickly divided like so:</p>

        <todo>nice picture of a chocoalate bar that has 3 by 6 = 18 square parts</todo>

        <figure>
            <image source = "images/division-chocolove-bar.JPG" width = "75%" />
        </figure>

        <p>The chocolate bar above has <m>3 \cdot 6 = 18</m> squares. If <m>2</m> people want to share this bar fairly, they divide the bar so that each person gets <m>18 \div 2 = 9</m> squares. The order of division matters<mdash />there's no way to divide the two people by the 18 squares. The order of division matters<mdash />division is <em>not</em> commutative.</p>

